Key Match Events: The Super Eagles lost 2-1 to Benin Republic in Abidjan in their fourth game in the 2026 FIFA World Cup qualifying series.
Post-Match Reflections: Senator John Owan Enoh expressed his dissatisfaction with the Super Eagles' performance, stating that the recent results are unacceptable.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Super Eagles secured only one point from a possible six in the June FIFA window, leaving them with a total of just three points from a possible twelve.
